cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with learning on sets of points in computer vision and graphics, specifically for recognition of handwritten digits and Chinese characters. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses kernel methods, which are commonly used in machine learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper deals with geometrical invariances and practical constraints associated with point clouds, which suggests it could belong to cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The paper also presents applications to recognition, suggesting it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses dynamic programming recursions, which suggests it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
